stylometry:
We are planning to minimize the costs of a restaurant related to labor hours. Problems we are trying to consider are the amount of employees that should be working on the different shifts, how many full-time and part-time employees should we have, and tryign to schedule each person enough to fulfill their worker status without having overtime.

The management problem is being able to schedule each worker according to their worker status without scheduling too many or too little employees in a day, satisfying employee schedule requests, and not having any overtime hours.
